Create a simple anonymous confession website called TGP Confessions that will be deployed on tgpconfessions.vercel.app.

The website should only allow users to submit confessions, similar to confessout.com. Users should not be able to view other confessions. The site must have a very clean and minimal interface.

The homepage should contain:

A title: “TGP Confessions”

A subtitle: “Share your confession anonymously”

An input field for Name (Only visible to admin)

A large textarea where users can write their confession

A Submit Confession button

Functionality requirements:

Users can submit a confession with their name.

The confession should be sent to a backend API.

The name and confession must be stored so that only the admin can see the name.

The public website must not display any confessions or names.

After submission, show a message: “Confession sent anonymously!”

Backend requirements:

Create an API endpoint /api/confess.

When a confession is submitted, store both name and confession.

The data should be visible only to the admin (for example through logs or an admin dashboard).

Design requirements:

Use a dark theme UI.

Background color: #0f172a

Card color: #1e293b

Accent button color: #ff2e63

Rounded inputs and buttons.

Structure of the project:

index.html for the submission page

style.css for styling

/api/confess.js for the backend function

The website should be mobile-friendly, minimal, and focused only on confession submission.